# 🎮 Nova64 - Ultimate 3D Fantasy Console Development Guide

> **⚠️ OUTDATED - This file is deprecated. Please refer to [AGENTS.md](./AGENTS.md) for the current cross-agent guide.**
>
> This file is kept for historical reference only. AGENTS.md is now the canonical source of truth for repository instructions.

This file provides comprehensive guidance for AI assistants working with the **Nova64 Ultimate 3D Fantasy Console** codebase. Current version: **0.4.8**.

## 🖥️ **Windows Development Environment**

**⚠️ IMPORTANT: On Windows machines, always use WSL (Windows Subsystem for Linux):**

```bash
# First, open WSL terminal, then set Node.js version
nvm use 20

# Now you can run pnpm commands
pnpm dev
```

**Key points:**

- Always use **WSL** on Windows (not PowerShell or CMD)
- Run `nvm use 20` before any pnpm commands in WSL
- All pnpm commands must be executed inside WSL
- Node.js 20 is required — other versions may break the build

## 🚀 **Development Commands**

**⚡ Always use `pnpm` for all package management and development tasks:**

```bash
# 📦 Install dependencies (ALWAYS use pnpm)
pnpm install

# 🔥 Start development server with hot reloading
pnpm dev            # http://localhost:5173  (serves console.html)

# 🏗️ Build for production (runs vite build + scripts/postbuild.js)
pnpm build

# 👁️ Preview production build
pnpm preview

# 🧪 Run complete test suite (505/505 tests passing)
pnpm test

# 🎯 Run specific test suites
pnpm test:api
pnpm test:input
pnpm test:starfox
pnpm test:integration
pnpm test:voxel
pnpm test:resize
pnpm test:cli
pnpm test:all        # alias for full suite
pnpm test:watch      # re-run on file changes

# 📊 Benchmarks
pnpm bench
pnpm bench:material
pnpm bench:instancing
pnpm bench:mesh

# 🔍 Lint / format
pnpm lint
pnpm lint:fix
pnpm format
```

**🚨 CRITICAL: Never use `npm` or `yarn` — always use `pnpm`.**

## 🛠️ **CLI Tool** (`bin/nova64.js`)

The Nova64 CLI provides project scaffolding, template cloning, and a dev server:

```bash
# Create a new empty project (prompts for name if omitted)
nova64 init my-game

# Browse and clone from 70+ example templates (interactive picker)
nova64 template

# Clone a specific template directly
nova64 template star-fox-nova-3d

# Start dev server in a project directory (serves code.js with hot reload)
cd my-game && nova64 dev

# Launch the full console with all demos (requires pnpm build first)
nova64 --start-demo    # Opens http://localhost:3000/console.html
```

### **CLI Architecture** (`bin/commands/`):

- `bin/nova64.js` - Main entry point with subcommand routing
- `bin/commands/init.js` - Project scaffolding (creates `code.js`, `package.json`, `index.html`)
- `bin/commands/template.js` - Interactive template picker using `@inquirer/prompts` with categorized list
- `bin/commands/dev.js` - Vite dev server that serves Nova64 runtime + user's `code.js` via `cart-runner.html`

### **Scaffolded Project Structure**:

```
my-game/
├── code.js        # Cart entry point (init/update/draw)
├── index.html     # HTML shell with import map
└── package.json   # Has nova64 dependency + "nova64 dev" script
```

## 🔍 **Debug Panel** (`runtime/debug-panel.js`)

An in-browser debug overlay for inspecting and editing scenes at runtime.

### **Activation**:

- Press **F9** to toggle the panel open/closed
- Add `?debug=1` to the URL to auto-open on load
- Install the [Three.js DevTools](https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/three-js-developer-tools/ljjomegalejmghcbeafmpnpgkoopignh) browser extension for additional scene inspection

### **Panel Sections**:

- **Time Controls** (toolbar): Pause/Resume, Step Frame, Reload Cart, Speed slider (0–2x)
- **Performance**: FPS, triangles, draw calls, geometries, textures, shader programs
- **Camera**: Editable position/target/FOV inputs (calls `setCameraPosition`/`setCameraTarget`/`setCameraFOV` live)
- **Scene Graph**: Collapsible tree of all objects — toggle visibility, click to highlight with wireframe bounding box
- **Inspector**: Click an object in the scene graph to edit position/rotation/scale, material color/opacity, wireframe toggle
- **Lights**: Color picker + intensity slider for every light in the scene
- **Console Log**: Captured `console.log`/`warn`/`error` output with color-coded entries and auto-scroll

### **Three.js DevTools Bridge** (`src/main.js`):

Exposes `globalThis.__THREE__`, `__THREE_SCENE__`, `__THREE_RENDERER__`, `__THREE_CAMERA__` so the browser extension can inspect the live scene.

## 🏗️ **Architecture Overview**

Nova64 is a **JavaScript 3D Fantasy Console** featuring:

- **🎯 3D Graphics Engine** powered by Three.js (with Babylon.js as an experimental backend)
- **⚡ 505/505 tests passing** (100% test coverage)
- **🎨 Nintendo 64/PlayStation Aesthetics** with modern performance
- **✨ Advanced Materials System** (holographic, metallic, emissive effects)
- **🌫️ Cinematic Lighting & Atmospherics** with 4K shadow mapping

### 🎯 **Core Components**

**GPU Backends** (`runtime/`):

- `gpu-threejs.js` - **Primary backend** — Three.js with advanced materials, lighting, shader systems, and 2D overlay compositing
- `gpu-babylon.js` - **Experimental Babylon.js backend** — parallel self-contained implementation; activate via `?backend=babylon` URL param or by serving `babylon_console.html`
- `gpu-webgl2.js` - **WebGL2 fallback** with RGBA16F textures and ACES tone mapping
- `gpu-canvas2d.js` - **Canvas2D fallback** with ordered dithering for maximum compatibility

**Backend Adapter Layer**:

- `engine-adapter.js` - Backend-agnostic adapter; exposes `engine` global so cart code never imports THREE directly
- `engine-adapter-babylon.js` - Babylon.js implementation of the adapter contract
- `framebuffer.js` - `Framebuffer64` — Uint16 RGBA pixel buffer; **required by all standard API modules** via `gpu.getFramebuffer()`

**Core Runtime**:

- `api.js` - Standard 2D drawing API (pset, line, rect, cls, print, etc.) — calls `gpu.getFramebuffer()`
- `api-2d.js` - Extended 2D canvas drawing API
- `api-3d.js` - 3D primitive API (createCube, setCameraPosition, rotateMesh, etc.)
- `api-generative.js` - Processing.js-style generative art (noise, ellipse, bezier, flow fields, matrix stack)
- `api-sprites.js` - 2D sprite system with GPU batching and parallax scrolling
- `api-effects.js` - Post-processing effects (bloom, vignette, chromatic aberration, glitch)
- `api-skybox.js` - Space, gradient, and solid sky backgrounds
- `api-blend.js` - Canvas2D blend mode constants and helpers
- `api-filters.js` - CSS/Canvas2D filter effects
- `api-particles-2d.js` - Sprite-textured 2D particle emitter
- `api-presets.js` - One-call visual style presets (N64 mode, PSX mode, low-poly)
- `api-gameutils.js` - Game utilities (shake, cooldowns, hit states, spawners, pools, state machines, timers, floating text)
- `api-voxel.js` - Full voxel engine with chunk streaming, biomes, fluid simulation, entity system, and pathfinding
- `console.js` - Main Nova64 class; dynamic ES module cart loading and hot reloading
- `input.js` - Input system: key(), btn(), btnp(), keyp() — keyboard + gamepad + mouse
- `font.js` - Bitmap font renderer
- `audio.js` - WebAudio system with spatial 3D audio and named SFX presets
- `physics.js` - AABB collision and gravity simulation
- `collision.js` - Raycasting and spatial partitioning
- `storage.js` - Persistent storage via localStorage with JSON serialization
- `textinput.js` - Text input overlay and keyboard handling
- `editor.js` - In-browser sprite and asset editor

**Display & Scene Systems**:

- `stage.js` - Flash/PixiJS-style display list for Canvas2D scene graphs
- `canvas-ui.js` - NML (Nova Markup Language) — XML-driven Canvas2D GUI system
- `camera-2d.js` - 2D camera system for stage rendering (pan, zoom, shake)
- `screens.js` - Screen state machine with animated transitions (fade, slide, wipe)
- `debug-panel.js` - F9 in-browser debug overlay
- `fullscreen-button.js` - Fullscreen toggle button

**Media & Assets**:

- `assets.js` / `asset-loader.js` - Asset loading pipeline
- `wad.js` - DOOM WAD file parser, level converter, and texture manager
- `movie-clip.js` - Flash-style sprite animation system
- `manifest.js` - Cart manifest loader

**Advanced Systems**:

- `xr.js` - WebXR (VR + AR) and Cardboard VR support
- `mediapipe.js` - MediaPipe Vision integration (hand, face, pose tracking)
- `hype.js` - HYPE animation framework (inspired by HYPE_AS3/Processing)
- `tween.js` - Unified tween engine used by Stage, HYPE, and cart code
- `store.js` - Zustand-powered reactive game state
- `namespace.js` - Nova64 namespace builder (nova64.* API surface)
- `ui.js` - UI system
- `nft-seed.js` - NFT seed-based generative art
- `i18n.js` - Internationalisation support
- `logger.js` - Structured logging (Nova64:INFO/WARN/ERROR)
- `env.js` - Environment detection
- `data.js` - Data utilities

### 🎮 **Cart System**

Nova64 carts are **ES modules** with three lifecycle hooks:

```javascript
let cube;

export function init() {
  // Create 3D objects ONCE here — never inside draw()
  cube = createCube(2, 0x0088ff, [0, 0, -5], { material: 'holographic' });
  setCameraPosition(0, 5, 10);
  setFog(0x1a1a2e, 10, 30);
}

export function update(dt) {
  // Handle input, update game logic, animate objects
  if (key('KeyW')) player.z -= 5 * dt;
  rotateMesh(cube, 0, dt, 0);
}

export function draw() {
  // 3D scene renders automatically — draw 2D HUD here
  print('Score: 1000', 10, 10, 0xffffff);
}
```

**Cart Loading**: Modify import path in `src/main.js` (line ~109) to test different demos.

**Babylon.js backend**: Load `babylon_console.html` or append `?backend=babylon` to any URL.

### 🏗️ **Key Architectural Patterns**

**GPU Contract**: Every GPU backend **must** implement:
- `getFramebuffer()` → returns a `Framebuffer64` instance (required by api.js, api-2d.js, api-generative.js)
- `supportsSpriteBatch()` → boolean
- `beginFrame()` / `endFrame()` → called each tick
- `resize(w, h)` → handle canvas resize

**Global API Exposure**: All runtime modules expose APIs via `.exposeTo(globalThis)`.

**Renderer Fallback Chain**:
1. **Three.js** (preferred) — full 3D, advanced materials and lighting
2. **Babylon.js** (experimental) — activate with `?backend=babylon`
3. **WebGL2** — high-performance 2D with shader effects
4. **Canvas2D** — universal compatibility fallback

**Color Pipeline**: 64-bit RGBA (Uint16 per channel). Helpers: `packRGBA64()`, `rgba8()`, `unpackRGBA64()`.

## 🎨 **Cart Development**

### Creating a new cart:

1. Create `examples/your-cart/code.js` with `init` / `update` / `draw` exports
2. Update cart path in `src/main.js:109` for hot reloading
3. Use control panel dropdown to switch between demos at runtime
4. Run `pnpm test` to validate (505/505 must pass)

### Complete Global API:

- **3D Graphics**: createCube(size,color,[x,y,z],opts), createSphere(), createPlane(), createCylinder(), createCone(), createCapsule(), createTorus()
- **Camera**: setCameraPosition(), setCameraTarget(), setCameraFOV()
- **Transforms**: rotateMesh(), setPosition(), setScale(), removeMesh() / destroyMesh()
- **Atmospherics**: setFog(), clearFog(), setAmbientLight(), createPointLight()
- **Input**: key(code), keyp(code), btn(i), btnp(i) — keyboard + gamepad + mouse
- **Skybox**: createSpaceSkybox(), createGradientSkybox(), createSolidSkybox(), enableSkyboxAutoAnimate()
- **Effects**: enableBloom(), enableVignette(), enableGlitch(), enableChromaticAberration(), enableN64Mode(), enablePSXMode(), enableLowPolyMode()
- **Audio**: sfx(preset), sfx({wave,freq,dur}), setVolume() — named presets: 'jump','coin','explosion',…
- **Storage**: saveData(key,val), loadData(key,fallback), deleteData(key)
- **Physics**: createBody(), stepPhysics(dt), setGravity(), setCollisionMap(fn)
- **Text**: print(), printCentered(), drawGlowText(), drawCrosshair(), drawProgressBar()
- **Minimap**: createMinimap(opts), drawMinimap(mm,time)
- **Tween**: tween(target, props, opts) — easing, chaining, onComplete
- **Screens**: pushScreen(id), popScreen(), registerScreen(id, {init,update,draw})
- **Game Utils**: createShake/triggerShake/updateShake, createCooldown/useCooldown/updateCooldowns, createHitState/triggerHit/isInvulnerable/isVisible, createSpawner/updateSpawner, createPool, createFloatingTextSystem/drawFloatingTexts/drawFloatingTexts3D, createStateMachine, createTimer
- **Voxel Engine**: BLOCK_TYPES, updateVoxelWorld(), forceLoadVoxelChunks(), resetVoxelWorld(), configureVoxelWorld(), getVoxelConfig(), getVoxelBlock(), setVoxelBlock(), getVoxelHighestBlock(), getVoxelBiome(), registerVoxelBlock(), getVoxelBlockShape(), getVoxelBlockBoundingBox(), isVoxelBlockFullCube(), VOXEL_SHAPE_BBOXES, raycastVoxelBlock(), checkVoxelCollision(), checkVoxelFluid(), moveVoxelEntity(), getVoxelLightLevel(), setVoxelDayTime(), setVoxelFluidSource(), removeVoxelFluidSource(), getVoxelFluidLevel(), spawnVoxelEntity(), removeVoxelEntity(), getVoxelEntity(), damageVoxelEntity(), healVoxelEntity(), updateVoxelEntities(), getVoxelEntitiesInRadius(), getVoxelEntitiesByType(), getVoxelEntityCount(), cleanupVoxelEntities(), setVoxelEntityComponent(), getVoxelEntityComponent(), hasVoxelEntityComponent(), removeVoxelEntityComponent(), queryVoxelEntities(), createVoxelEntityArchetype(), spawnVoxelEntityFromArchetype(), findVoxelPath(), exportVoxelRegion(), importVoxelRegion(), exportVoxelWorldJSON(), importVoxelWorldJSON(), saveVoxelWorld(), loadVoxelWorld(), listVoxelWorlds(), deleteVoxelWorld(), enableVoxelTextures(), loadVoxelTextureAtlas(), simplexNoise2D(), simplexNoise3D(), placeVoxelTree()

